      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The Lee stablemates from Victoria could hold the key to this. JILLIBY DOOLEY (5) is a lightly-raced but progressive colt who has come from wider barriers to win both starts off a spell, the latest at Terang on Tuesday when he worked before drawing clear to score by 5m. Led in the previous outing so can push forward from this barrier. Jason Lee drives him over the stablemate so that could be a push. KEAYANG PASSION (4) was very good in the NSW Oaks series, placing in her heat before coming from wider than this for fourth in the final. Had kicked off her career with a string of top-two finishes in Victoria and SA prior. Big chance from a good draw. BETTORLEFTALONE (11) cops a wide draw but is on the up and came from this barrier to score at this circuit and distance last start, his second victory on the trot. PAPI ROCKS (6) should be fitter for her winning return at Goulburn and is lightly raced with upside.",
